ed files | 0 | 0 (2 pre-existing non-nav artifacts hub-wide out of scope) |\n95: | Batches committed + pushed to v4 | 11 | 11/11 |\n96: \n97: **Verification Date**: 2026-07-12\n98: <!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->\n\n(End of file - total 98 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Checklist: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\ndescription: \"QA verification checklist for the sk-code split-doc conformance, with evidence.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"019 checklist sk-code split doc\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-12T14:23:42Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"All checklist items verified\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Terminal gates\"\n---\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: checklist | v2.2 -->\n\n# Checklist: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/checklist.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Checklist: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\ndescription: \"QA verification checklist for the sk-code split-doc conformance, with evidence.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"019 checklist sk-code split doc\"\nimportance_tier: \"normal\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-12T14:23:42Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"All checklist items verified\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Terminal gates\"\n---\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: checklist | v2.2 -->\n\n# Checklist: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:protocol -->\n## Verification Protocol\nEvery item carries a command + result. Deterministic checkers only.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:protocol -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n## Pre-Implementation\n- [x] Templates + package_skill.py read as authority\n- [x] 027 collision scope confirmed (no active fight)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n## Code Quality\n- [x] Renames are snake_case, path-segment only; content preserved (frontmatter/OVERVIEW added, sections renumbered)\n- [x] 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version on every conformed file\n- [x] Comment hygiene: no spec paths/ids embedded in doc content\n<!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## Testing\n- [x] validate_document.py 0 issues on all 163 sk-code ref+asset files\n- [x] 0 hyphenated split filenames remaining\n- [x] 0 broken .md links to/among the renamed files — every conformed file and its referrers resolve\n- [x] 2 pre-existing non-navigational artifacts hub-wide are out of this packet's scope: an illustrative `005-example.com` example path (`webflow_constraints.md`) and a bare filename quoted in changelog prose (`changelog/v3.3.0.0.md`) — both predate this work, neither is a rename referrer\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n## Fix Completeness\n- [x] All in-scope files/packets processed; no partial batch left uncommitted\n- [x] Every verification gate passed before the batch was committed\n<!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n## Security\n- [x] Documentation-only; no executable/tooling changes; no new capabilities\n<!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n## Documentation\n- [x] Batch commits carry evidence in messages; spec/plan/tasks/summary consistent\n<!-- /ANCHOR:docs -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:file-org -->\n## File Organization\n- [x] Whole-hub staging captures cross-surface reference-link fixes (process fix after early per-surface staging dropped 2)\n- [x] Zero edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment\n<!-- /ANCHOR:file-org -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:summary -->\n## Verification Summary\n\n| Category | Total | Verified |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| sk-code ref+asset files conformed | 163 | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n| Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 | 0 |\n| Broken .md links to/among renamed files | 0 | 0 (2 pre-existing non-nav artifacts hub-wide out of scope) |\n| Batches committed + pushed to v4 | 11 | 11/11 |\n\n**Verification Date**: 2026-07-12\n<!-- /ANCHOR:summary -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":98,"totalLines":98,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/checklist.md","time":{"start":1783921172535,"end":1783921172559}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04cc24bcb82b7017016a547a146b0c81918fd40d4f79f0df33"}},"id":"prt_f59fce027001bWuYd9IKVvkAr8","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f59fca0fe001XHGiEuUxdvrvHS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921172563,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_OWvAgl32TnkTp6veEzftLApP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Implementation Summary: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\n3: description: \"Conformed all 163 mechanically-split reference/asset files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the create-skill asset/reference templates: snake_case renames, 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, OVERVIEW wrapper, content preserved, every in-hub reference updated. Executed by GPT-5.6-sol-fast in an isolated worktree, orchestrator-verified per batch; 0 hyphenated names, 0 broken links to renamed files; committed + pushed to v4. Post-ship 10-iteration deep review (GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH) drove two P1 remediations: 21 code-webflow Purpose paragraphs de-duplicated from their H1 intro, and the broken-link completion claim narrowed to its true renamed-file scope.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"019 summary sk-code split doc alignment\"\n6: importance_tier: \"important\"\n7: contextType: \"implementation\"\n8: _memory:\n9:   continuity:\n10:     packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n11:     last_updated_at: \"2026-07-13T05:12:00Z\"\n12:     last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n13:     recent_action: \"xHigh verification remediation: 4 structural fixes\"\n14:     next_safe_action: \"Commit + push\"\n15:     blockers: []\n16:     completion_pct: 100\n17:     status: \"Complete\"\n18: ---\n19: # Implementation Summary\n20: \n21: <!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n22: <!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: impl-summary-core | v2.2 -->\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: <!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n27: ## Metadata\n28: | Field | Value |\n29: |-------|-------|\n30: | **Packet** | 019 — sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment |\n31: | **Status** | Complete |\n32: | **Track** | sk-code |\n33: <!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: <!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n38: ## What Was Built\n39: All 163 mechanically-split reference/asset `.md` files across the three sk-code surfaces conformed to the create-skill templates.\n40: \n41: | Surface | Files | Result |\n42: |---|---|---|\n43: | code-quality (assets) | 3 | conformed |\n44: | code-opencode (refs+assets) | 65 | conformed |\n45: | code-webflow (refs+assets) | 95 | conformed |\n46: | **Total** | **163** | **163/163 at 0 issues** |\n47: \n48: Each file: hyphen→underscore rename (snake_case), 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, H1 + intro + `## 1. OVERVIEW` (Purpose/When-to-Use for refs, Purpose/Usage for assets), content sections renumbered (content preserved verbatim), and every in-hub reference to renamed files updated.\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n54: ## How It Was Delivered\n55: Serial GPT-5.6-sol-fast batches (opencode, --variant medium) in an isolated worktree, one subtree per batch (batches serialize on each surface's shared SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP). The orchestrator verified each batch (validate_document 0 + full-hub broken-link scan) and committed the whole hub before dispatching the next. Every batch committed + pushed to v4.\n56: <!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: <!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n61: ## Key Decisions\n62: - **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n63: - **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n64: - **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n65: - **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n66: - **xHigh triplicate verification → four more structural fixes the HIGH pass missed.** Three parallel GPT-5.6-sol-fast xHigh lineages (concurrency 3) re-reviewed the remediated tree and agreed on four in-scope defects, each bounded to one file/row by re-scan: the rust `interop_errors_and_parity.md` had its `## 1. OVERVIEW` scaffold appended at the file's end after 11 orphaned `###` content sections — restructured so OVERVIEW leads and content sits under numbered `## 2.`–`## 12.` sections; one containment duplicate (`overview_hls_and_lenis.md`) the first de-dup scan missed — Purpose rewritten; the whole-hub link claim survived in this summary's own verification table (checklist was fixed, summary table was not) — narrowed; and an asset README trigger phrase (\"code README\") was not lowercase — corrected.\n67: <!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: <!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n72: ## Verification\n73: | Check | Result |\n74: |---|---|\n75: | validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n76: | Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n77: | Broken relative .md links to/among renamed files | 0 (2 pre-existing non-navigational artifacts hub-wide out of scope) |\n78: | Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: <!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n84: ## Known Limitations\n85: - The surface SKILL.md files (code-opencode/code-webflow) still FAIL `package_skill.py --check` for a pre-existing reason (deliberate surface-packet headers, not the create-skill required-section names) — out of scope; per-file resource-doc conformance verified via validate_document.py instead.\n86: - `validate.sh --strict` returns exit 1 (warnings), not exit 0: the packet carries pre-existing warning-tier items (checklist rows without inline evidence markers, section-count/complexity heuristics). This is the accepted completion bar for this packet (Errors: 0); a deep-review lineage rated the warning cluster P1, but it predates this work and is not a conformance defect in the deliverable.\n87: <!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## Post-Completion Follow-Up\n92: - Sibling `sk-doc/017-smart-routing-mechanism-notes` completes Request 2.\n93: - **Out-of-scope content follow-ups surfaced by the xHigh verification review** (structural template-alignment is this packet's scope; content correctness is not — recommend a separate content-quality pass): a security reference (`code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md`) labels a JavaScript-set session cookie both good and bad in the same doc; a third-party example (`code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md`) sets `script.src` from arbitrary input without an allowlist or `integrity`; and ~19 references carry a generic \"when implementing or troubleshooting <title>\" When-to-Use rather than concrete scenarios. None were authored by the mechanical split; all predate this packet.\n\n(End of file - total 93 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Summary: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\ndescription: \"Conformed all 163 mechanically-split reference/asset files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the create-skill asset/reference templates: snake_case renames, 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, OVERVIEW wrapper, content preserved, every in-hub reference updated. Executed by GPT-5.6-sol-fast in an isolated worktree, orchestrator-verified per batch; 0 hyphenated names, 0 broken links to renamed files; committed + pushed to v4. Post-ship 10-iteration deep review (GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH) drove two P1 remediations: 21 code-webflow Purpose paragraphs de-duplicated from their H1 intro, and the broken-link completion claim narrowed to its true renamed-file scope.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"019 summary sk-code split doc alignment\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-13T05:12:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"xHigh verification remediation: 4 structural fixes\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Commit + push\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    status: \"Complete\"\n---\n# Implementation Summary\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Summary: sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment\"\ndescription: \"Conformed all 163 mechanically-split reference/asset files under sk-code/{code-opencode,code-webflow,code-quality} to the create-skill asset/reference templates: snake_case renames, 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, OVERVIEW wrapper, content preserved, every in-hub reference updated. Executed by GPT-5.6-sol-fast in an isolated worktree, orchestrator-verified per batch; 0 hyphenated names, 0 broken links to renamed files; committed + pushed to v4. Post-ship 10-iteration deep review (GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH) drove two P1 remediations: 21 code-webflow Purpose paragraphs de-duplicated from their H1 intro, and the broken-link completion claim narrowed to its true renamed-file scope.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"019 summary sk-code split doc alignment\"\nimportance_tier: \"important\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-13T05:12:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"xHigh verification remediation: 4 structural fixes\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Commit + push\"\n    blockers: []\n    completion_pct: 100\n    status: \"Complete\"\n---\n# Implementation Summary\n\n<!-- SPECKIT_LEVEL: 2 -->\n<!-- SPECKIT_TEMPLATE_SOURCE: impl-summary-core | v2.2 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:metadata -->\n## Metadata\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Packet** | 019 — sk-code Split-Doc Template Alignment |\n| **Status** | Complete |\n| **Track** | sk-code |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:metadata -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-built -->\n## What Was Built\nAll 163 mechanically-split reference/asset `.md` files across the three sk-code surfaces conformed to the create-skill templates.\n\n| Surface | Files | Result |\n|---|---|---|\n| code-quality (assets) | 3 | conformed |\n| code-opencode (refs+assets) | 65 | conformed |\n| code-webflow (refs+assets) | 95 | conformed |\n| **Total** | **163** | **163/163 at 0 issues** |\n\nEach file: hyphen→underscore rename (snake_case), 5-field frontmatter + 4-part version, H1 + intro + `## 1. OVERVIEW` (Purpose/When-to-Use for refs, Purpose/Usage for assets), content sections renumbered (content preserved verbatim), and every in-hub reference to renamed files updated.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-built -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n## How It Was Delivered\nSerial GPT-5.6-sol-fast batches (opencode, --variant medium) in an isolated worktree, one subtree per batch (batches serialize on each surface's shared SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP). The orchestrator verified each batch (validate_document 0 + full-hub broken-link scan) and committed the whole hub before dispatching the next. Every batch committed + pushed to v4.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:how-delivered -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:decisions -->\n## Key Decisions\n- **Recurse into nested split dirs.** Verification caught GPT initially skipping nested `<lang>/quality_standards/` split dirs; every subsequent batch prompt made recursion explicit.\n- **Whole-hub staging.** Early per-surface `git add <surface>` commits dropped cross-surface reference-link fixes, leaving 2 broken links on v4; switched to staging the whole sk-code hub per commit and repaired them.\n- **snake_case per operator + 027.** Renames use underscore, aligning with the concurrent 027 naming migration (which had not covered these reference/asset split files).\n- **Post-ship deep review → two P1 remediations.** A 10-iteration GPT-5.6-sol-fast HIGH review (verdict FAIL, convergence 1.0) surfaced two confirmed P1s that the structural validators could not catch. F001: 21 code-webflow references had `### Purpose` copied verbatim from the H1 intro, violating the create-skill template's explicit non-duplication rule — each Purpose was rewritten to a section-derived, intro-distinct statement (0 duplicates across all 163). F002: the completion claim overstated \"0 broken links hub-wide\"; a fenced-code-aware scan found two pre-existing non-navigational artifacts (an illustrative `005-example.com` example path and a filename quoted in changelog prose, both authored by prior commits) — the claim was narrowed to its true renamed-file scope rather than editing correct documentation.\n- **xHigh triplicate verification → four more structural fixes the HIGH pass missed.** Three parallel GPT-5.6-sol-fast xHigh lineages (concurrency 3) re-reviewed the remediated tree and agreed on four in-scope defects, each bounded to one file/row by re-scan: the rust `interop_errors_and_parity.md` had its `## 1. OVERVIEW` scaffold appended at the file's end after 11 orphaned `###` content sections — restructured so OVERVIEW leads and content sits under numbered `## 2.`–`## 12.` sections; one containment duplicate (`overview_hls_and_lenis.md`) the first de-dup scan missed — Purpose rewritten; the whole-hub link claim survived in this summary's own verification table (checklist was fixed, summary table was not) — narrowed; and an asset README trigger phrase (\"code README\") was not lowercase — corrected.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n## Verification\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| validate_document.py on all sk-code ref+asset files | 163/163 at 0 issues |\n| Hyphenated split filenames remaining | 0 |\n| Broken relative .md links to/among renamed files | 0 (2 pre-existing non-navigational artifacts hub-wide out of scope) |\n| Edits under system-deep-loop/deep-alignment | None |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n## Known Limitations\n- The surface SKILL.md files (code-opencode/code-webflow) still FAIL `package_skill.py --check` for a pre-existing reason (deliberate surface-packet headers, not the create-skill required-section names) — out of scope; per-file resource-doc conformance verified via validate_document.py instead.\n- `validate.sh --strict` returns exit 1 (warnings), not exit 0: the packet carries pre-existing warning-tier items (checklist rows without inline evidence markers, section-count/complexity heuristics). This is the accepted completion bar for this packet (Errors: 0); a deep-review lineage rated the warning cluster P1, but it predates this work and is not a conformance defect in the deliverable.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n\n---\n\n## Post-Completion Follow-Up\n- Sibling `sk-doc/017-smart-routing-mechanism-notes` completes Request 2.\n- **Out-of-scope content follow-ups surfaced by the xHigh verification review** (structural template-alignment is this packet's scope; content correctness is not — recommend a separate content-quality pass): a security reference (`code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md`) labels a JavaScript-set session cookie both good and bad in the same doc; a third-party example (`code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md`) sets `script.src` from arbitrary input without an allowlist or `integrity`; and ~19 references carry a generic \"when implementing or troubleshooting <title>\" When-to-Use rather than concrete scenarios. None were authored by the mechanical split; all predate this packet.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":93,"totalLines":93,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/implementation-summary.md","time":{"start":1783921172540,"end":1783921172561}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04cc24bcb82b7017016a547a146b108191bd130eae0ea1eef6"}},"id":"prt_f59fce038001Cdstyfj5XzDQLK","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f59fca0fe001XHGiEuUxdvrvHS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921172566,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_eVAwkcDVNhdNojhVSR3VRU9k","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n2: # This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n3: # convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n4: # and validation expectations.\n5: \n6: meta:\n7:   ownerSkill: deep-review\n8:   reviewModeVersion: 2\n9:   generatedNotice:\n10:     warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n11:   sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n12: \n13: # Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\n14: contract:\n15:   defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n16: \n17:   contextSnapshot:\n18:     requiredAtInit: true\n19:     ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n20:     section: Known Context\n21:     source: bounded-review-context-snapshot\n22:     bounded: true\n23:     pointerBased: true\n24:     includes:\n25:       - targetPointers\n26:       - behaviorClaims\n27:       - reuseAndConventionPointers\n28:       - riskAreasAndContextGaps\n29:     forbids:\n30:       - deepContextDispatch\n31:       - fullSourceBodyInlining\n32:       - contextLoopReportCreation\n33:       - scopeWideningBeyondReviewTarget\n34: \n35:   # Review target taxonomy.\n36:   targetTypes:\n37:     - id: spec-folder\n38:       cliValue: spec-folder\n39:       label: Spec Folder\n40:       description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n41:     - id: skill\n42:       cliValue: skill\n43:       label: Skill\n44:       description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n45:     - id: agent\n46:       cliValue: agent\n47:       label: Agent\n48:       description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n49:     - id: track\n50:       cliValue: track\n51:       label: Track\n52:       description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n53:     - id: files\n54:       cliValue: files\n55:       label: Files\n56:       description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n57: \n58:   # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n59:   # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n60:   dimensions:\n61:     - id: correctness\n62:       priority: 1\n63:       label: Correctness\n64:       checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n65:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n66:     - id: security\n67:       priority: 2\n68:       label: Security\n69:       checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n70:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n71:     - id: traceability\n72:       priority: 3\n73:       label: Traceability\n74:       checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n75:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n76:     - id: maintainability\n77:       priority: 4\n78:       label: Maintainability\n79:       checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n80:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n81: \n82:   # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n83:   severities:\n84:     - id: P0\n85:       weight: 10.0\n86:       label: Blocker\n87:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n88:     - id: P1\n89:       weight: 5.0\n90:       label: Required\n91:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n92:     - id: P2\n93:       weight: 1.0\n94:       label: Suggestion\n95:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n96: \n97:   # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n98:   verdicts:\n99:     - id: FAIL\n100:       label: Fail\n101:       condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n102:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n103:     - id: CONDITIONAL\n104:       label: Conditional\n105:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n106:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n107:     - id: PASS\n108:       label: Pass\n109:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n110:       hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n111:       nextCommand: /create:changelog\n112: \n113:   # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n114:   qualityGates:\n115:     - id: evidence\n116:       label: Evidence\n117:       binary: true\n118:       combines:\n119:         - evidence-completeness\n120:         - no-inference-only\n121:       rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n122:     - id: scope\n123:       label: Scope\n124:       binary: true\n125:       combines:\n126:         - scope-alignment\n127:       rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n128:     - id: coverage\n129:       label: Coverage\n130:       binary: true\n131:       combines:\n132:         - severity-coverage\n133:         - cross-reference\n134:       rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n135: \n136:   # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n137:   convergence:\n138:     defaults:\n139:       maxIterations: 7\n140:       convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n141:       stuckThreshold: 2\n142:     signals:\n143:       - id: rolling-average\n144:         weight: 0.30\n145:         description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n146:       - id: mad-noise-floor\n147:         weight: 0.25\n148:         description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n149:       - id: dimension-coverage\n150:         weight: 0.45\n151:         description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n152:     severityMath:\n153:       refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n154:       p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n155:       noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n156:     coverageAge:\n157:       minStabilizationPasses: 1\n158:     thresholds:\n159:       rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n160:       noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n161:       compositeStopScore: 0.60\n162: \n163:   lifecycleModes:\n164:     - id: new\n165:       description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n166:     - id: resume\n167:       description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n168:     - id: restart\n169:       description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n170:     - id: fork\n171:       status: deferred\n172:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n173:     - id: completed-continue\n174:       status: deferred\n175:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n176: \n177:   lineageFields:\n178:     - sessionId\n179:     - parentSessionId\n180:     - lineageMode\n181:     - generation\n182:     - continuedFromRun\n183: \n184:   reducer:\n185:     enabled: true\n186:     inputs:\n187:       - latestJSONLDelta\n188:       - newIterationFile\n189:       - priorReducedState\n190:     outputs:\n191:       - findingsRegistry\n192:       - dashboardMetrics\n193:       - strategyUpdates\n194:     failureModes:\n195:       malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n196:       missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n197:       schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n198:     idempotent: true\n199: \n200:   releaseReadinessStates:\n201:     - id: in-progress\n202:       description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n203:     - id: converged\n204:       description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n205:     - id: release-blocking\n206:       description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n207: \n208:   # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n209:   # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n210:   crossReferenceProtocols:\n211:     - id: spec_code\n212:       dimension: traceability\n213:       level: core\n214:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n215:       gateClass: hard\n216:       passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n217:       partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n218:       failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n219:     - id: checklist_evidence\n220:       dimension: traceability\n221:       level: core\n222:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n223:       gateClass: hard\n224:       passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n225:       partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n226:       failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n227:     - id: skill_agent\n228:       dimension: traceability\n229:       level: overlay\n230:       appliesTo: [skill]\n231:       gateClass: advisory\n232:       passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n233:       partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n234:       failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n235:     - id: agent_cross_runtime\n236:       dimension: traceability\n237:       level: overlay\n238:       appliesTo: [agent]\n239:       gateClass: advisory\n240:       passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n241:       partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n242:       failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n243:     - id: feature_catalog_code\n244:       dimension: traceability\n245:       level: overlay\n246:       appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n247:       gateClass: advisory\n248:       passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n249:       partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n250:       failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n251:     - id: playbook_capability\n252:       dimension: traceability\n253:       level: overlay\n254:       appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n255:       gateClass: advisory\n256:       passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n257:       partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n258:       failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n259: \n260:   # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n261:   outputs:\n262:     config:\n263:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n264:       machineOwned: false\n265:       fields:\n266:         - sessionId\n267:         - parentSessionId\n268:         - lineageMode\n269:         - generation\n270:         - continuedFromRun\n271:         - releaseReadinessState\n272:     findingsRegistry:\n273:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n274:       machineOwned: true\n275:       sections:\n276:         - openFindings\n277:         - resolvedFindings\n278:         - repeatedFindings\n279:         - dimensionCoverage\n280:         - findingsBySeverity\n281:         - convergenceScore\n282:     reviewReport:\n283:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n284:       sections:\n285:         - executive-summary\n286:         - planning-trigger\n287:         - active-finding-registry\n288:         - remediation-workstreams\n289:         - spec-seed\n290:         - plan-seed\n291:         - traceability-status\n292:         - deferred-items\n293:         - audit-appendix\n294:     strategy:\n295:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n296:       requiredSections:\n297:         - topic\n298:         - review-dimensions\n299:         - completed-dimensions\n300:         - running-findings\n301:         - what-worked\n302:         - what-failed\n303:         - exhausted-approaches\n304:         - ruled-out-directions\n305:         - next-focus\n306:         - known-context\n307:         - cross-reference-status\n308:         - files-under-review\n309:         - review-boundaries\n310:     dashboard:\n311:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n312:       machineOwned: true\n313:       sections:\n314:         - status\n315:         - findings-summary\n316:         - dimension-coverage\n317:         - progress\n318:         - next-focus\n319:     pauseSentinel:\n320:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n321:       machineOwned: false\n322:       description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n323:     jsonl:\n324:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n325:       iterationRecord:\n326:         required:\n327:           - type\n328:           - mode\n329:           - run\n330:           - status\n331:           - focus\n332:           - dimensions\n333:           - filesReviewed\n334:           - findingsCount\n335:           - findingsSummary\n336:           - findingsNew\n337:           - findingDetails\n338:           - newFindingsRatio\n339:           - sessionId\n340:           - generation\n341:           - lineageMode\n342:           - timestamp\n343:           - durationMs\n344:         optional:\n345:           - parentSessionId\n346:           - continuedFromRun\n347:           - findingsRefined\n348:           - findingRefs\n349:           - traceabilityChecks\n350:           - coverage\n351:           - noveltyJustification\n352:           - ruledOut\n353:           - focusTrack\n354:           - scoreEstimate\n355:           - segment\n356:           - convergenceSignals\n357:           - graphEvents\n358:       synthesisEvent:\n359:         required:\n360:           - type\n361:           - event\n362:           - mode\n363:           - totalIterations\n364:           - verdict\n365:           - activeP0\n366:           - activeP1\n367:           - activeP2\n368:           - dimensionCoverage\n369:           - stopReason\n370:           - timestamp\n371: \n372: # Render targets define machine-generated contract fragments. Exactly one\n373: # target is real: the human-readable snapshot rendered by\n374: # render-contract-snapshot.cjs. Everything else that mentions this contract's\n375: # taxonomy (target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, quality gates,\n376: # convergence, cross-reference protocols) is hand-authored — see\n377: # authoredArtifacts below, not rendered from this file.\n378: render:\n379:   artifacts:\n380:     - id: review-contract-snapshot\n381:       path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n382:       ownership: generated\n383:       generator: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/render-contract-snapshot.cjs\n384:       format: markdown\n385:       markers:\n386:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n387:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n388:       sections:\n389:         - meta\n390:         - target-types\n391:         - dimensions\n392:         - severities\n393:         - verdicts\n394:         - quality-gates\n395:         - convergence\n396:         - cross-reference-protocols\n397:         - outputs\n398:         - validation\n399: \n400: # Authored artifacts reference this manifest's taxonomy in hand-written prose\n401: # or YAML. They are not machine-rendered and carry no generated markers;\n402: # operators keep them in sync by hand when this contract changes. Each\n403: # entry's enumParityChecked list is mechanically enforced (not aspirational):\n404: # deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts confirms every id in those families\n405: # still appears literally in the target file, as a lightweight drift\n406: # tripwire that does not require full rendering.\n407: authoredArtifacts:\n408:   - id: workflow-auto\n409:     path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\n410:     ownership: authored\n411:     format: yaml\n412:     enumParityChecked:\n413:       - dimensions\n414:       - severities\n415:       - verdicts\n416:       - cross-reference-protocols\n417:     note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :auto command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n418:   - id: workflow-confirm\n419:     path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml\n420:     ownership: authored\n421:     format: yaml\n422:     enumParityChecked:\n423:       - dimensions\n424:       - severities\n425:       - verdicts\n426:       - cross-reference-protocols\n427:     note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :confirm command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n428:   - id: agent-opencode\n429:     path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n430:     ownership: authored\n431:     format: markdown\n432:     enumParityChecked:\n433:       - dimensions\n434:       - severities\n435:       - verdicts\n436:     note: Hand-maintained OpenCode agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n437:   - id: agent-claude\n438:     path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n439:     ownership: authored\n440:     format: markdown\n441:     enumParityChecked:\n442:       - dimensions\n443:       - severities\n444:       - verdicts\n445:     note: Hand-maintained Claude Code agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n446:   - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n447:     path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n448:     ownership: authored\n449:     format: markdown\n450:     enumParityChecked:\n451:       - dimensions\n452:       - severities\n453:       - verdicts\n454:     note: Hand-maintained quick reference. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n455: \n456: # Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\n457: validation:\n458:   schemaVersion: 1\n459:   checks:\n460:     - id: schema\n461:       description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n462:     - id: render-verify\n463:       description: \"Re-render the single review-contract-snapshot artifact (node render-contract-snapshot.cjs --check) and fail on drift. The five authoredArtifacts entries are hand-maintained and are not re-rendered by this check.\"\n464:     - id: marker-integrity\n465:       description: Ensure the review-contract-snapshot artifact contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n466:     - id: enum-parity\n467:       description: \"Confirm the dimension, severity, and verdict ids (plus cross-reference-protocol ids for the two workflow YAMLs) declared in each authoredArtifacts entry's enumParityChecked are still literally present in that file; see deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts.\"\n468:     - id: jsonl-parity\n469:       description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n470:     - id: lifecycle-parity\n471:       description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n472:     - id: reducer-contract\n473:       description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n474:     - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n475:       description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n476:     - id: runtime-coverage\n477:       description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared authoredArtifacts entry and parity coverage.\n478:     - id: playbook-assertions\n479:       description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.\n\n(End of file - total 479 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  contextSnapshot:\n    requiredAtInit: true\n    ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n    section: Known Context","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","text":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  contextSnapshot:\n    requiredAtInit: true\n    ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n    section: Known Context\n    source: bounded-review-context-snapshot\n    bounded: true\n    pointerBased: true\n    includes:\n      - targetPointers\n      - behaviorClaims\n      - reuseAndConventionPointers\n      - riskAreasAndContextGaps\n    forbids:\n      - deepContextDispatch\n      - fullSourceBodyInlining\n      - contextLoopReportCreation\n      - scopeWideningBeyondReviewTarget\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:\n    - id: spec-folder\n      cliValue: spec-folder\n      label: Spec Folder\n      description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n    - id: skill\n      cliValue: skill\n      label: Skill\n      description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n    - id: agent\n      cliValue: agent\n      label: Agent\n      description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n    - id: track\n      cliValue: track\n      label: Track\n      description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n    - id: files\n      cliValue: files\n      label: Files\n      description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n\n  # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n  # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n  dimensions:\n    - id: correctness\n      priority: 1\n      label: Correctness\n      checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: security\n      priority: 2\n      label: Security\n      checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: traceability\n      priority: 3\n      label: Traceability\n      checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n    - id: maintainability\n      priority: 4\n      label: Maintainability\n      checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n\n  # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n  severities:\n    - id: P0\n      weight: 10.0\n      label: Blocker\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P1\n      weight: 5.0\n      label: Required\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P2\n      weight: 1.0\n      label: Suggestion\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n\n  # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n  verdicts:\n    - id: FAIL\n      label: Fail\n      condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: CONDITIONAL\n      label: Conditional\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: PASS\n      label: Pass\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n      hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n      nextCommand: /create:changelog\n\n  # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n  qualityGates:\n    - id: evidence\n      label: Evidence\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - evidence-completeness\n        - no-inference-only\n      rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n    - id: scope\n      label: Scope\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - scope-alignment\n      rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n    - id: coverage\n      label: Coverage\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - severity-coverage\n        - cross-reference\n      rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n\n  # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n  convergence:\n    defaults:\n      maxIterations: 7\n      convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n      stuckThreshold: 2\n    signals:\n      - id: rolling-average\n        weight: 0.30\n        description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n      - id: mad-noise-floor\n        weight: 0.25\n        description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n      - id: dimension-coverage\n        weight: 0.45\n        description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n    severityMath:\n      refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n      p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n      noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n    coverageAge:\n      minStabilizationPasses: 1\n    thresholds:\n      rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n      noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n      compositeStopScore: 0.60\n\n  lifecycleModes:\n    - id: new\n      description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n    - id: resume\n      description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n    - id: restart\n      description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n    - id: fork\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n    - id: completed-continue\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n\n  lineageFields:\n    - sessionId\n    - parentSessionId\n    - lineageMode\n    - generation\n    - continuedFromRun\n\n  reducer:\n    enabled: true\n    inputs:\n      - latestJSONLDelta\n      - newIterationFile\n      - priorReducedState\n    outputs:\n      - findingsRegistry\n      - dashboardMetrics\n      - strategyUpdates\n    failureModes:\n      malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n      missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n      schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n    idempotent: true\n\n  releaseReadinessStates:\n    - id: in-progress\n      description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n    - id: converged\n      description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n    - id: release-blocking\n      description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n\n  # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n  # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n  crossReferenceProtocols:\n    - id: spec_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n      partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n      failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n    - id: checklist_evidence\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n      partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n      failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n    - id: skill_agent\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n      partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n      failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n    - id: agent_cross_runtime\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [agent]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n      partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n      failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n    - id: feature_catalog_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n      partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n      failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n    - id: playbook_capability\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings\n        - resolvedFindings\n        - repeatedFindings\n        - dimensionCoverage\n        - findingsBySeverity\n        - convergenceScore\n    reviewReport:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n      sections:\n        - executive-summary\n        - planning-trigger\n        - active-finding-registry\n        - remediation-workstreams\n        - spec-seed\n        - plan-seed\n        - traceability-status\n        - deferred-items\n        - audit-appendix\n    strategy:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n      requiredSections:\n        - topic\n        - review-dimensions\n        - completed-dimensions\n        - running-findings\n        - what-worked\n        - what-failed\n        - exhausted-approaches\n        - ruled-out-directions\n        - next-focus\n        - known-context\n        - cross-reference-status\n        - files-under-review\n        - review-boundaries\n    dashboard:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - status\n        - findings-summary\n        - dimension-coverage\n        - progress\n        - next-focus\n    pauseSentinel:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n    jsonl:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n      iterationRecord:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - mode\n          - run\n          - status\n          - focus\n          - dimensions\n          - filesReviewed\n          - findingsCount\n          - findingsSummary\n          - findingsNew\n          - findingDetails\n          - newFindingsRatio\n          - sessionId\n          - generation\n          - lineageMode\n          - timestamp\n          - durationMs\n        optional:\n          - parentSessionId\n          - continuedFromRun\n          - findingsRefined\n          - findingRefs\n          - traceabilityChecks\n          - coverage\n          - noveltyJustification\n          - ruledOut\n          - focusTrack\n          - scoreEstimate\n          - segment\n          - convergenceSignals\n          - graphEvents\n      synthesisEvent:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - event\n          - mode\n          - totalIterations\n          - verdict\n          - activeP0\n          - activeP1\n          - activeP2\n          - dimensionCoverage\n          - stopReason\n          - timestamp\n\n# Render targets define machine-generated contract fragments. Exactly one\n# target is real: the human-readable snapshot rendered by\n# render-contract-snapshot.cjs. Everything else that mentions this contract's\n# taxonomy (target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, quality gates,\n# convergence, cross-reference protocols) is hand-authored — see\n# authoredArtifacts below, not rendered from this file.\nrender:\n  artifacts:\n    - id: review-contract-snapshot\n      path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n      ownership: generated\n      generator: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/render-contract-snapshot.cjs\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n      sections:\n        - meta\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n        - validation\n\n# Authored artifacts reference this manifest's taxonomy in hand-written prose\n# or YAML. They are not machine-rendered and carry no generated markers;\n# operators keep them in sync by hand when this contract changes. Each\n# entry's enumParityChecked list is mechanically enforced (not aspirational):\n# deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts confirms every id in those families\n# still appears literally in the target file, as a lightweight drift\n# tripwire that does not require full rendering.\nauthoredArtifacts:\n  - id: workflow-auto\n    path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml\n    ownership: authored\n    format: yaml\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n      - cross-reference-protocols\n    note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :auto command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: workflow-confirm\n    path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_confirm.yaml\n    ownership: authored\n    format: yaml\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n      - cross-reference-protocols\n    note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :confirm command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: agent-opencode\n    path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained OpenCode agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: agent-claude\n    path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained Claude Code agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n    path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained quick reference. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n\n# Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\nvalidation:\n  schemaVersion: 1\n  checks:\n    - id: schema\n      description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n    - id: render-verify\n      description: \"Re-render the single review-contract-snapshot artifact (node render-contract-snapshot.cjs --check) and fail on drift. The five authoredArtifacts entries are hand-maintained and are not re-rendered by this check.\"\n    - id: marker-integrity\n      description: Ensure the review-contract-snapshot artifact contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n    - id: enum-parity\n      description: \"Confirm the dimension, severity, and verdict ids (plus cross-reference-protocol ids for the two workflow YAMLs) declared in each authoredArtifacts entry's enumParityChecked are still literally present in that file; see deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts.\"\n    - id: jsonl-par