{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921643132,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_xM1Avm9m3LWdmxAqIyeADbDs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"eval\\(|new Function\\(|exec\\(|innerHTML\\s*=|localStorage\\.setItem\\(['\\\"](?:token|password|secret)|chmod 777|rm -rf|curl .+\\|\\s*(?:bash|sh)","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 22 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/plugins_and_hooks/post_edit_quality_router.md:\n  Line 108: rm -rf \"$TMPDIR_LIVE\"\n\n  Line 114:    reusing Command 2's `$TMPDIR_LIVE` -- Command 2's own trailing `rm -rf \"$TMPDIR_LIVE\"` already\n\n  Line 129: rm -rf \"$TMPDIR_KILL\"\n\n  Line 167: rm -rf \"$TMPDIR_LIVE\"\n\n  Line 190: rm -rf /private/tmp/mk-post-edit-quality-outside-root-check\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/shared/dev_workflow/automation_errors_and_compat.md:\n  Line 252: // Risk: element.innerHTML = userInput\n\n  Line 258: element.innerHTML = sanitizeHTML(userInput); // Sanitized\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/tooling_and_hooks/comment_hygiene_hook.md:\n  Line 49:    rm -rf \"$SANDBOX\"; mkdir -p \"$SANDBOX\"\n\n  Line 81:    rm -rf \"$SANDBOX\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/owasp_prototype_and_safe_access.md:\n  Line 323: - ❌ Use eval(), Function(), or execute user input\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md:\n  Line 49: element.innerHTML = sanitize_html(user_input);\n\n  Line 53: element.innerHTML = user_input;  // XSS vulnerability!\n\n  Line 62: element.innerHTML = user_input;  // Unnecessary risk\n\n  Line 87: - [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n\n  Line 151: exec(user_command);  // Command injection vulnerability!\n\n  Line 156: // ❌ BAD: eval() with user input\n\n  Line 157: eval(user_input);  // Extreme vulnerability\n\n  Line 160: new Function(user_input)();  // Also vulnerable\n\n  Line 169: - [ ] Never use eval(), Function(), or execute user input\n\n  Line 245: localStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\n\n  Line 246: localStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/shared/references/universal/error_recovery.md:\n  Line 79: - Lockfile not corrupt (`rm -rf node_modules && npm ci` for JS / TS).\n","metadata":{"matches":22,"truncated":false},"title":"eval\\(|new Function\\(|exec\\(|innerHTML\\s*=|localStorage\\.setItem\\(['\\\"](?:token|password|secret)|chmod 777|rm -rf|curl .+\\|\\s*(?:bash|sh)","time":{"start":1783921643103,"end":1783921643130}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d3405cd983171bf016a547beaf1c8819196dfe641f34cc7dc"}},"id":"prt_f5a040e45001iiD229xKW67WoK","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f5a03d015001PUuLSXJNb5bUMA"}}
