{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921655001,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_IpimqTJUF1mQnBGYAinVXwbi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/resource_loading.md","offset":270,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/resource_loading.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n270: \n271: ### Visual Timeline\n272: \n273: ```\n274: Without attribute (blocking):\n275: HTML: ----[PAUSE]----[PAUSE]----\n276: JS:        [download][execute]\n277: \n278: With async:\n279: HTML: ----------------[PAUSE]---\n280: JS:   [download]      [execute]\n281: \n282: With defer:\n283: HTML: -------------------------[execute]\n284: JS:   [download]               ^DOM ready\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### When to Use Each\n288: \n289: | Strategy | Use For |\n290: |----------|---------|\n291: | No attribute | Inline scripts, critical blocking scripts |\n292: | `async` | Independent scripts (analytics, ads) |\n293: | `defer` | Scripts that need DOM, order-dependent scripts |\n294: | Dynamic | Conditional loading, lazy loading |\n295: \n296: ### Implementation Example\n297: \n298: ```html\n299: <!-- defer: needs DOM, order matters -->\n300: <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-bundle.min.js\" defer></script>\n301: ```\n302: \n303: ### Dynamic Script Loading\n304: \n305: ```javascript\n306: function loadScript(src, options = {}) {\n307:   return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n308:     const script = document.createElement('script');\n309:     script.src = src;\n310:     script.async = options.async ?? true;\n311: \n312:     if (options.type) script.type = options.type;\n313:     if (options.crossorigin) script.crossOrigin = 'anonymous';\n314: \n315:     script.onload = resolve;\n316:     script.onerror = reject;\n317: \n318:     document.head.appendChild(script);\n319:   });\n320: }\n321: \n322: // Usage\n323: loadScript('https://example.com/analytics.js')\n324:   .then(() => console.log('Analytics loaded'))\n325:   .catch(() => console.warn('Analytics failed to load'));\n326: ```\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ## 8. NOSCRIPT FALLBACKS\n331: \n332: Always provide fallbacks for JavaScript-dependent loading:\n333: \n334: ```html\n335: <!-- Async CSS with fallback -->\n336: <link rel=\"preload\" href=\"style.css\" as=\"style\" onload=\"this.rel='stylesheet'\">\n337: <noscript><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"style.css\"></noscript>\n338: \n339: <!-- Lazy-loaded images with fallback -->\n340: <img data-src=\"image.webp\" class=\"lazyload\" alt=\"Description\">\n341: <noscript><img src=\"image.webp\" alt=\"Description\"></noscript>\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: ## 9. DECISION MATRIX\n347: \n348: | Resource Type | Strategy | Reason |\n349: |---------------|----------|--------|\n350: | Critical CSS | Inline or `<link>` in `<head>` | Blocks render (intentionally) |\n351: | Below-fold CSS | Async pattern | Non-blocking, no FOUC |\n352: | Critical JS | Preload + defer | High priority + non-blocking |\n353: | DOM-dependent JS | defer | Executes after DOM ready |\n354: | Independent JS | async | Executes when ready |\n355: | Analytics/Ads | requestIdleCallback + async | Non-critical |\n356: | Fonts | Preconnect + preload | Prevents FOUT |\n357: | Hero images | Preload | LCP optimization |\n358: | Below-fold images | Native lazy loading | Saves bandwidth |\n359: | Third-party origins | Preconnect | Saves connection time |\n\n(Showing lines 270-359 of 443. Use offset=360 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n### Visual Timeline\n\n```\nWithout attribute (blocking):\nHTML: ----[PAUSE]----[PAUSE]----\nJS:        [download][execute]\n\nWith async:\nHTML: ----------------[PAUSE]---\nJS:   [download]      [execute]\n\nWith defer:\nHTML: -------------------------[execute]\nJS:   [download]               ^DOM ready\n```\n\n### When to Use Each\n\n| Strategy | Use For |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/resource_loading.md","text":"\n### Visual Timeline\n\n```\nWithout attribute (blocking):\nHTML: ----[PAUSE]----[PAUSE]----\nJS:        [download][execute]\n\nWith async:\nHTML: ----------------[PAUSE]---\nJS:   [download]      [execute]\n\nWith defer:\nHTML: -------------------------[execute]\nJS:   [download]               ^DOM ready\n```\n\n### When to Use Each\n\n| Strategy | Use For |\n|----------|---------|\n| No attribute | Inline scripts, critical blocking scripts |\n| `async` | Independent scripts (analytics, ads) |\n| `defer` | Scripts that need DOM, order-dependent scripts |\n| Dynamic | Conditional loading, lazy loading |\n\n### Implementation Example\n\n```html\n<!-- defer: needs DOM, order matters -->\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/swiper@11/swiper-bundle.min.js\" defer></script>\n```\n\n### Dynamic Script Loading\n\n```javascript\nfunction loadScript(src, options = {}) {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const script = document.createElement('script');\n    script.src = src;\n    script.async = options.async ?? true;\n\n    if (options.type) script.type = options.type;\n    if (options.crossorigin) script.crossOrigin = 'anonymous';\n\n    script.onload = resolve;\n    script.onerror = reject;\n\n    document.head.appendChild(script);\n  });\n}\n\n// Usage\nloadScript('https://example.com/analytics.js')\n  .then(() => console.log('Analytics loaded'))\n  .catch(() => console.warn('Analytics failed to load'));\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. NOSCRIPT FALLBACKS\n\nAlways provide fallbacks for JavaScript-dependent loading:\n\n```html\n<!-- Async CSS with fallback -->\n<link rel=\"preload\" href=\"style.css\" as=\"style\" onload=\"this.rel='stylesheet'\">\n<noscript><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"style.css\"></noscript>\n\n<!-- Lazy-loaded images with fallback -->\n<img data-src=\"image.webp\" class=\"lazyload\" alt=\"Description\">\n<noscript><img src=\"image.webp\" alt=\"Description\"></noscript>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 9. DECISION MATRIX\n\n| Resource Type | Strategy | Reason |\n|---------------|----------|--------|\n| Critical CSS | Inline or `<link>` in `<head>` | Blocks render (intentionally) |\n| Below-fold CSS | Async pattern | Non-blocking, no FOUC |\n| Critical JS | Preload + defer | High priority + non-blocking |\n| DOM-dependent JS | defer | Executes after DOM ready |\n| Independent JS | async | Executes when ready |\n| Analytics/Ads | requestIdleCallback + async | Non-critical |\n| Fonts | Preconnect + preload | Prevents FOUT |\n| Hero images | Preload | LCP optimization |\n| Below-fold images | Native lazy loading | Saves bandwidth |\n| Third-party origins | Preconnect | Saves connection time |","lineStart":270,"lineEnd":359,"totalLines":443,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/performance/resource_loading.md","time":{"start":1783921654992,"end":1783921655000}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a54407d7d43b232016a547bf6cf2c8191865602ad633bd63e"}},"id":"prt_f5a043c9b001xVVXbEfqOtt8Nq","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f5a04144900164RCmxzSkoDz3R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921655053,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WUuuZfcBarCo0Dwg31vItTDw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/overview_hls_and_lenis.md","offset":20,"limit":55},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/overview_hls_and_lenis.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Entry point for integrating external JavaScript libraries into Webflow: the shared integration principles and script-loading pattern, plus concrete setups for HLS.js (video streaming) and Lenis (smooth scroll).\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: - Integrating new third-party libraries\n28: - Managing dependencies (CDN, versions)\n29: - Handling external script loading\n30: \n31: ### Integration Principles\n32: \n33: 1. **CDN-first loading** - Use jsDelivr or unpkg for reliable delivery\n34: 2. **Version pinning** - Always pin to specific versions for stability\n35: 3. **Feature detection** - Check library availability before use\n36: 4. **Graceful fallbacks** - Handle missing/failed libraries gracefully\n37: 5. **Memory management** - Proper cleanup to prevent leaks\n38: \n39: ### Loading Pattern\n40: \n41: ```javascript\n42: const LIBRARY_CDN_URL = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/library@{version}';\n43: \n44: async function load_library() {\n45:   if (typeof window.Library !== 'undefined') {\n46:     return true;\n47:   }\n48: \n49:   return new Promise((resolve) => {\n50:     const script = document.createElement('script');\n51:     script.src = LIBRARY_CDN_URL;\n52:     script.async = true;\n53:     script.onload = () => resolve(true);\n54:     script.onerror = () => resolve(false);\n55:     document.head.appendChild(script);\n56:   });\n57: }\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 2. HLS.JS (VIDEO STREAMING)\n63: \n64: HTTP Live Streaming library for adaptive video playback in non-Safari browsers.\n65: \n66: ### CDN URL\n67: \n68: ```html\n69: <!-- Preload for critical video pages -->\n70: <link rel=\"preload\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hls.js@{version}\" as=\"script\">\n71: \n72: <!-- Load with defer -->\n73: <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hls.js@{version}\" defer></script>\n74: ```\n\n(Showing lines 20-74 of 215. Use offset=75 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nEntry point for integrating external JavaScript libraries into Webflow: the shared integration principles and script-loading pattern, plus concrete setups for HLS.js (video streaming) and Lenis (smooth scroll).\n\n### When to Use\n- Integrating new third-party libraries\n- Managing dependencies (CDN, versions)\n- Handling external script loading\n\n### Integration Principles\n\n1. **CDN-first loading** - Use jsDelivr or unpkg for reliable delivery\n2. **Version pinning** - Always pin to specific versions for stability\n3. **Feature detection** - Check library availability before use\n4. **Graceful fallbacks** - Handle missing/failed libraries gracefully\n5. **Memory management** - Proper cleanup to prevent leaks\n\n### Loading Pattern","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/overview_hls_and_lenis.md","text":"## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nEntry point for integrating external JavaScript libraries into Webflow: the shared integration principles and script-loading pattern, plus concrete setups for HLS.js (video streaming) and Lenis (smooth scroll).\n\n### When to Use\n- Integrating new third-party libraries\n- Managing dependencies (CDN, versions)\n- Handling external script loading\n\n### Integration Principles\n\n1. **CDN-first loading** - Use jsDelivr or unpkg for reliable delivery\n2. **Version pinning** - Always pin to specific versions for stability\n3. **Feature detection** - Check library availability before use\n4. **Graceful fallbacks** - Handle missing/failed libraries gracefully\n5. **Memory management** - Proper cleanup to prevent leaks\n\n### Loading Pattern\n\n```javascript\nconst LIBRARY_CDN_URL = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/library@{version}';\n\nasync function load_library() {\n  if (typeof window.Library !== 'undefined') {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const script = document.createElement('script');\n    script.src = LIBRARY_CDN_URL;\n    script.async = true;\n    script.onload = () => resolve(true);\n    script.onerror = () => resolve(false);\n    document.head.appendChild(script);\n  });\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. HLS.JS (VIDEO STREAMING)\n\nHTTP Live Streaming library for adaptive video playback in non-Safari browsers.\n\n### CDN URL\n\n```html\n<!-- Preload for critical video pages -->\n<link rel=\"preload\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hls.js@{version}\" as=\"script\">\n\n<!-- Load with defer -->\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hls.js@{version}\" defer></script>\n```","lineStart":20,"lineEnd":74,"totalLines":215,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/overview_hls_and_lenis.md","time":{"start":1783921655042,"end":1783921655051}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a54407d7d43b232016a547bf6d278819198e500511b8576a9"}},"id":"prt_f5a043cf2001dvt0veS75vaKK6","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f5a04144900164RCmxzSkoDz3R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921655099,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2FwtlCQR9s9izHlXF3oz3Oc9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/botpoison_and_finsweet.md","offset":35,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/botpoison_and_finsweet.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n35: Invisible captcha alternative for form spam protection without user friction.\n36: \n37: ### CDN URL\n38: \n39: ```javascript\n40: const BOTPOISON_SDK_URL = 'https://unpkg.com/@botpoison/browser';\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ### Loading Pattern\n44: \n45: The SDK is loaded lazily on first form submission to avoid blocking page load.\n46: \n47: ```javascript\n48: // Source: src/javascript/form/form_submission.js:47-117\n49: let botpoison_loader = null;\n50: \n51: async function load_botpoison_sdk() {\n52:   if (typeof window.Botpoison !== 'undefined') {\n53:     return true;\n54:   }\n55: \n56:   // Deduplicate concurrent load requests\n57:   if (botpoison_loader) {\n58:     return botpoison_loader;\n59:   }\n60: \n61:   botpoison_loader = new Promise((resolve) => {\n62:     const script = document.createElement('script');\n63:     script.src = BOTPOISON_SDK_URL;\n64:     script.async = true;\n65:     script.onload = () => resolve(true);\n66:     script.onerror = () => resolve(false);  // Graceful degradation\n67:     document.head.appendChild(script);\n68:   }).then((loaded) => {\n69:     if (!loaded) {\n70:       botpoison_loader = null;  // Allow retry on failure\n71:     }\n72:     return loaded;\n73:   });\n74: \n75:   return botpoison_loader;\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Challenge Flow with Timeout\n80: \n81: The challenge solving includes timeout protection and client instance caching.\n82: \n83: ```javascript\n84: // Source: src/javascript/form/form_submission.js:119-179\n\n(Showing lines 35-84 of 438. Use offset=85 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Invisible captcha alternative for form spam protection without user friction.\n\n### CDN URL\n\n```javascript\nconst BOTPOISON_SDK_URL = 'https://unpkg.com/@botpoison/browser';\n```\n\n### Loading Pattern\n\nThe SDK is loaded lazily on first form submission to avoid blocking page load.\n\n```javascript\n// Source: src/javascript/form/form_submission.js:47-117\nlet botpoison_loader = null;\n\nasync function load_botpoison_sdk() {\n  if (typeof window.Botpoison !== 'undefined') {\n    return true;\n  }","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/botpoison_and_finsweet.md","text":"Invisible captcha alternative for form spam protection without user friction.\n\n### CDN URL\n\n```javascript\nconst BOTPOISON_SDK_URL = 'https://unpkg.com/@botpoison/browser';\n```\n\n### Loading Pattern\n\nThe SDK is loaded lazily on first form submission to avoid blocking page load.\n\n```javascript\n// Source: src/javascript/form/form_submission.js:47-117\nlet botpoison_loader = null;\n\nasync function load_botpoison_sdk() {\n  if (typeof window.Botpoison !== 'undefined') {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Deduplicate concurrent load requests\n  if (botpoison_loader) {\n    return botpoison_loader;\n  }\n\n  botpoison_loader = new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const script = document.createElement('script');\n    script.src = BOTPOISON_SDK_URL;\n    script.async = true;\n    script.onload = () => resolve(true);\n    script.onerror = () => resolve(false);  // Graceful degradation\n    document.head.appendChild(script);\n  }).then((loaded) => {\n    if (!loaded) {\n      botpoison_loader = null;  // Allow retry on failure\n    }\n    return loaded;\n  });\n\n  return botpoison_loader;\n}\n```\n\n### Challenge Flow with Timeout\n\nThe challenge solving includes timeout protection and client instance caching.\n\n```javascript\n// Source: src/javascript/form/form_submission.js:119-179","lineStart":35,"lineEnd":84,"totalLines":438,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/botpoison_and_finsweet.md","time":{"start":1783921655095,"end":1783921655098}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a54407d7d43b232016a547bf6d52881918f7505ecc596a797"}},"id":"prt_f5a043d03001pa0vVZT0uioTx0","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f5a04144900164RCmxzSkoDz3R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783921655196,"sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Yqloc2UJkQEzr7fPMXVNThKa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/async_patterns/timing_compat_and_webflow.md","offset":175,"limit":42},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/async_patterns/timing_compat_and_webflow.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n175:             init_analytics();\n176:             init_scroll_tracking();\n177:         }, { timeout: 3000 });\n178:     } else {\n179:         setTimeout(function() {\n180:             init_analytics();\n181:             init_scroll_tracking();\n182:         }, 2000);\n183:     }\n184: });\n185: ```\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## 5. REAL EXAMPLE: GTM DELAY\n190: \n191: ```javascript\n192: (function() {\n193:     function load_gtm() {\n194:         // GTM initialization code\n195:         var script = document.createElement('script');\n196:         script.src = 'https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id=GTM-XXXX';\n197:         document.head.appendChild(script);\n198:     }\n199: \n200:     if ('requestIdleCallback' in window) {\n201:         requestIdleCallback(load_gtm, { timeout: 3000 });\n202:     } else {\n203:         setTimeout(load_gtm, 2000);\n204:     }\n205: })();\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n211: \n212: ### Internal References\n213: \n214: - [implementation_workflows.md](../implementation_workflows/condition_based_waiting.md) - Condition-based waiting patterns\n215: - [performance_patterns.md](../performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md) - Throttle/debounce and performance optimization\n216: - [../performance/third_party.md](../../performance/third_party.md) - Third-party script loading optimization\n\n(Showing lines 175-216 of 223. Use offset=217 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"            init_analytics();\n            init_scroll_tracking();\n        }, { timeout: 3000 });\n    } else {\n        setTimeout(function() {\n            init_analytics();\n            init_scroll_tracking();\n        }, 2000);\n    }\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. REAL EXAMPLE: GTM DELAY\n\n```javascript\n(function() {\n    function load_gtm() {\n        // GTM initialization code","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/async_patterns/timing_compat_and_webflow.md","text":"            init_analytics();\n            init_scroll_tracking();\n        }, { timeout: 3000 });\n    } else {\n        setTimeout(function() {\n            init_analytics();\n            init_scroll_tracking();\n        }, 2000);\n    }\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. REAL EXAMPLE: GTM DELAY\n\n```javascript\n(function() {\n    function load_gtm() {\n        // GTM initialization code\n        var script = document.createElement('script');\n        script.src = 'https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtm.js?id=GTM-XXXX';\n        document.head.appendChild(script);\n    }\n\n    if ('requestIdleCallback' in window) {\n        requestIdleCallback(load_gtm, { timeout: 3000 });\n    } else {\n        setTimeout(load_gtm, 2000);\n    }\n})();\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n### Internal References\n\n- [implementation_workflows.md](../implementation_workflows/condition_based_waiting.md) - Condition-based waiting patterns\n- [performance_patterns.md](../performance_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md) - Throttle/debounce and performance optimization\n- [../performance/third_party.md](../../performance/third_party.md) - Third-party script loading optimization","lineStart":175,"lineEnd":216,"totalLines":223,"truncated":true}},"titl