-c/deep-review-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-c/deep-review-strategy.md\n@@ -42,12 +42,14 @@\n ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n \n - Initialization: direct packet reads established the current claims and prior-remediation targets after memory retrieval timed out.\n - Iteration 1: deterministic scans covered all 163 paths; forced resource validation, opening-shape checks, link resolution, and direct evidence reads isolated one P1 and one P2 class.\n+- Iteration 2: exact security searches and direct trust-boundary reads confirmed the prior cookie and CDN remediations and ruled out adjacent unsafe-guidance classes.\n \n ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n \n - Memory trigger retrieval timed out; the bounded context snapshot uses current packet and source pointers instead.\n+- Security searches initially surfaced bad-example snippets; direct context reads were required to distinguish prohibited demonstrations from endorsed guidance.\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n ### `checklist_evidence` (core): **fail, provisional** - validator success is real but does not establish pre-Overview ordering; final replay is scheduled for iteration 3. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n@@ -122,8 +124,9 @@\n - Reuse and conventions: create-skill reference/asset templates and `validate_document.py` are the named authorities.\n - Risk areas: earlier reviews found a missing Overview wrapper, overlong intros, tautological When-to-Use guidance, contradictory session-cookie guidance, and an under-constrained CDN loader; the packet now claims the in-scope structural items were fixed.\n - Missing context: Spec Kit Memory retrieval timed out; no packet-level `resource-map.md` exists.\n - Iteration 1 carry-forward: `C1-P1-001` remains active at `code-webflow/references/shared/enforcement.md:19-24`; `C1-P2-001` covers eight lexical paths/five resolved documents with three-sentence intros.\n+- Iteration 2 carry-forward: no new finding; the prior cookie and CDN guidance defects are resolved, while the active correctness P1/P2 remain unchanged.\n - Out of scope: surface `SKILL.md` header shape and unrelated deep-loop artifacts.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:known-context -->\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:cross-reference-status -->\n","additions":3,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-c/prompts/iteration-002.md\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-c/iterations/iteration-002.md\nA .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-c/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-c/deep-review-state.jsonl\nM .opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-confirm/lineages/confirm-c/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783921725086,"end":1783921725098}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_015d57f4171ed821016a547c0750c481918d4068ddf733273d"}},"id":"prt_f5a047ca8001KxF2ph6SiQ90bV","sessionID":"ses_0a60505fdffeqSdEmZI11c4h43","messageID":"msg_f5a044205001bTlWQfCGHJlysk"}}
